##Can live selling cars save car companies?

Micro Signal biz-leaders

Function introduction, define Chinese commercial power

By ruoyi Guo
Source: biz-leaders

By ruoyi Guo

Source: biz-leaders

Hot

BMW began its first night live broadcast at its tmall flagship store at 7 pm on Tuesday. Two sales staff wearing masks, suits, each holding a doll, toward the camera to chat.

The studio soon reached more than 3,000 viewers. Unlike the more adept hosts of games and entertainment, these two hosts look a bit awkward. From the car model, screen interaction, to the end of the lottery, an hour of live broadcast, it seems to be listening to a "cross talk" after the end of the announcement.

The car salesman "ducked" into the online live studio is still continuing the new crown pneumonia epidemic. With offline sales basically stagnated, the car industry is already in the depths of winter, open the online market has become many car companies and dealers had to make a breakthrough choice.

"I didn't expect the live broadcast to be so popular. Recently, many auto manufacturers have been consulting us about whether there is a live broadcast function, " Liu Feng, who works on a large car vertical platform, told business people.

He says his team has been working on a new project since starting work on Feb. 3 -- a live streaming product for manufacturers. The product was supposed to start slowly in a few years, but the company is working overtime to get it up and running in March.

Like many of the industries hit by the outbreak, auto makers are having a hard time.

According to the federation, 1.69 million passenger cars were sold nationwide in January, down 21.5 percent from the same month last year, the lowest growth rate since the organization began keeping statistics in 2005. Since February, the impact of the epidemic is more obvious, the entire automotive industry chain is almost in a state of complete standstill. According to the latest survey by the China Automobile Circulation Association, the Composite Rework rate of 68 car dealer groups (involving a total of 4,4374s stores across the country) is only about 10 percent. Although car companies and dealers have resumed work, but the first quarter of a sharp decline in production and sales will be inevitable.

The face of the door can be empty offline sales stores, including a number of foreign investment, joint ventures and domestic brands, including the car manufacturers, will have their eyes on the line. "The cloud sees a car" , VR panoramic sees a car, on-line order and Book on-site test drive wait for on-line action, become very hot for a time.

ŌKAWA, who has worked in a mainframe factory for many years, said he learned from inside the industry that, "In fact, live car sales have been tried before the outbreak, and from the resumption of work until now, many car companies have set a hard target for online live streaming. As a low-cost way to get customers, this has become something that must be done at present. "

A person related to sales of Xiaopeng Automobile told "business people" that since the implementation of its online sales program, each store has started to broadcast live car talks one by one, official micro, Douyin, Kuaishou official account and other channels are also carried out. On average, the official accounts broadcast at least one live broadcast per week, and the store's own plan to broadcast an average of more than eight live broadcasts per day. As of February 11,30 stores had conducted live car-watching and car-speaking.

Hard nut

Liu Feng's intuitive feeling is that before many car manufacturers do not attach much importance to online marketing. Now affected by the epidemic, online demand has become very strong. Although Douyin, tmall platform traffic is huge, but some manufacturers out of the consideration of product tonality, still want to live through the industry vertical platform. "It was in response to this demand that the company decided to launch a b-side live product as soon as possible. "We may be selling the service as a package, and the vendor will get the traffic and the clues [ that is, the valid phone numbers ] when they buy the live feed. "

At present on the market the live broadcast sells the vehicle mainly by two kind of teams are doing. One is carried out by the salesman of the manufacturer, one is the nature of the goods, that is, the manufacturer and Kol Cooperation. This is similar to a small group purchase, by Kol early online acquisition of car needs, save to two hundred when to negotiate with manufacturers to get a better purchase price.

There is no doubt that extra pressure will be put on the sales staff of these companies, who are not very good at internal performance. Compared with the past user to the store number, orders and turnover of the assessment indicators, now in the face of the camera, live room activity and intention of the number of users, it may become a new thorny task.

Although all kinds of live situation lively, but either way, to seize the current wave of traffic dividend are not easy.

In ŌKAWA's view, the traditional 4s shop sales model is offline orders, and there is no online ordering process, the actual delivery is still needed to the store. In the 4S shop to buy a variety of costs calculated more miscellaneous, taking into account a variety of configuration, insurance, and verbal concessions, the transaction price and guidance price can be thirty thousand yuan difference. The price is so opaque that orders can not be placed directly online. In addition, the current 4s shop sales are regional, is a different interest groups, and does not support the delivery of cars in different places. If you place an order online in one place, but need another place to connect, the whole process becomes complicated.

"Many of the live broadcast sales are now done in order to fulfill the KPI and live broadcast. Basic live broadcast requirements such as camera sense, skills, product presentation and so on are relatively deficient and have not been properly trained, " he said, from the point of view of most users, the car is after all one hundred thousand, one hundred thousand large goods, to the store on the spot is still just need. The biggest role of live streaming is to channel, but orders still need to be sold offline or other forms to better achieve.

Online live broadcast conversion rate is not high, from Liu Feng has been exposed to some cases can also see clues. He said that from the past several times with the vendor experience, online sales are more general effect. Live streaming, which usually takes the form of giving out coupons, doesn't necessarily count as a better deal than going to the store. Live broadcast of the use of marketing costs, the final "wool or out on the sheep. ". Live streaming is not a good fit for a product like cars, which may have a lot of traffic, but conversion rates and useful leads are not ideal. Consumers are more likely to consult online, then go to a physical store to experience and finally close the deal.

In addition, he also believes that in the case of "cross-regional sales" is strictly prohibited, manufacturers or resellers are not interested in the order of a different place. For example, a buyer from Hunan Province placed an order from Jiangxi Province, but now they can not go out, so car buyers can only digest it locally. It's impossible to close a deal on live TV without making it to the store.

"At this stage, live car sales may be more of a gimmick, for products with the flow can be, but the actual conversion effect is difficult to assess, " Liu Feng said.

Differentiation

Price transparency, word-of-mouth and branding become apparent when you can't touch a real car. The new powers, with their uniform pricing and direct channels, are seen as better suited to live streaming and are likely to have higher conversion rates than traditional carmakers.

At present in addition to the small Peng Automobile, Wei Lai and Wilma have also joined the live broadcast camp. Tesla, who appears to be on top of the world, switched to live car sales long before he temporarily closed all offline stores in mainland China on Feb. 2.

Xiaopeng said the above-mentioned people, different from traditional car dealers rely on offline store sales channels, Xiaopeng automotive online content and user operations have some experience. The key now is to drive traffic up by optimizing the live streaming process and ultimately drive orders. From the current flow conversion point of view, stay clues, test driving appointment and intention to order, or even large orders, are harvested.

However, it did not disclose further sales figures.

Although Ōkawa thinks the effectiveness of live streaming is up in the air, he thinks the pattern may hold after the epidemic is over. Even car companies should set up a fixed operation team, to be responsible for this part of the work. In particular, if all manufacturers are supporting online orders, then live car sales and other online marketing is likely to become the focus of the driving force.

"The current cost of a 4s store is high, and the fixed monthly cost of a larger store can be more than three million per month, " according to a new report from Boston Consulting Group, some weak brands, new brands and high inventory of dealers in particular face survival challenges. Therefore, in the view of the industry, to expand the sales channel online, it is a future change in the sales system step.

Liu Feng is part of a team of less than 20 people, is stepping up the live product testing. He also felt the huge potential demand behind the incomplete live-streaming of car sales. "It turns out that some vendors are slow to respond to this stuff online because they don't lack customers. But now there's a shift in perception, and it's important to realize that it's also important to be online. Such a shift would not have happened in the short term if it had not been for the extremes of the epidemic."

For fast-moving, forward-thinking vendors, online marketing may also accelerate the transformation of their business model, including the allocation of marketing costs. And the original solidification of the car advertising market, will also be generated by this new wave. Liu Feng for example, the current car manufacturers a clue to the cost of about 200-500 yuan, if all kinds of online platform diversion and transformation effect, which will no doubt provide more possibilities for its market strategy.

Thursday, February 20th. BMW IS BACK ON TMALL for four full-day live shows. At the other end of the douyin platform, all kinds of cars Kol also explained to fans of various models of "hard core" knowledge. How far can car companies go in the winter amid the general anxiety that the epidemic has engendered?

(pseudonyms include Liu Feng and Ōkawa)
